caption: I get sad when they are not open! Get that breakfast sandwich with the pork! Also they have spiked coffee for you party in the morning people!
Blessed to live down the block from here. Great food, great coffee, and a bunch of cool groceries. Staff is super nice. A proper gem.
I’m plant based, but their chicken sandwich is 100% worth eating meat.
Vietnamese coffee!!!! They have Vietnamese coffee and it’s actually good!!! Love this place will try more things in the future!!!
Great addition to the neighborhood. Highly recommended.
The breakfast sandwich from here is hands down my favorite breakfast in all of brooklyn. No...in all of NYC! With a Vietnamese coffee on the side. This place is a must!! Service is also great.

This place is new to me and amazing! So convenient to have a mini Asian grocery store in the neighborhood. Their food is amazing, love the whitefish sandwich!! Don’t miss the boozy cocktails. Staff is super friendly and knowledgeable. Thanks!
The breakfast sandwich gave me life 😭🖤

This place is amazing! I thought I didn’t like congee and I was completely wrong. The congee is incredible, the place itself is adorable and they also have a ton of great staples in the market area. You can also grab an espresso or Vietnamese coffee while you’re there :) Such a positive place!
The congee is so delicious and comforting. Love the cute look inside too. Definitely going to frequent this spot.
I order the pork and broccoli with a little spice sandwich it was amazing..
I'd never had congee before trying this place and it was delicious! Will definitely be ordering from here again and trying other dishes on the menu.

I wish I could leave a review with no stars! I ordered a vanilla iced coffee with cream, very light. After seeing others that came after me ( who happened to be white) leave with their orders, I inquired about my order, it hadn’t been made. I had to reiterate my order only to be told they don’t have cream. I don’t drink milk but conceded to it because I was just ready to leave. When I asked did the coffee have vanilla, the barista looked at the cashier to confirm I paid for it, at that point I told them they could keep it and walked away. No one offered a refund or explanation for what I just encountered! Reprehensible behavior, the nerve to display a minority owned sign in the window.
You don’t know what heaven tastes like until you have the breakfast spicy pork sandwich.
This cafe is so warm and cozy, the staff is incredible.
Delicious delicious delicious.  Super flavorful & thoughtful food that gives you a true feeling of comfort!  Sweet staff too :)
Absolute fire 🙏🏼 I inhaled my congee. The black sesame latte is very delicious as well as refreshing. Thank you 💕
One of my favorite neighborhood spots. The congee bowls are amazing! I love the selection of groceries that can be purchased. Definitely a great addition to bedstuy!
Love the Vietnamese iced coffe ♥️
I had the stewed pork congee bowl which was incredible then played the wonderful owner in Mahjong... she beat me twice. I can’t wait to return.
amazing congees and coffee!
Great Coffee and a cool atmosphere.
:) I love our congee, our shop, our peoples.
Nice place but no bathroom.
Strong flavors, great value, good atmosphere. They played Stevie Wonder, so how could I not love it?
I ordered brasied chicken congee. The staff is warm and kind. Food was great and delicious. All thise fresh ingredients were absolutely good for health.

Really loved the congee at Maya! Interesting take on the often plain uninspired rice porridge. It's pricey but worth it for the enormous serving and indulgent ingredients. I'd give it 5 stars but... they serve everything in plastic containers even when you eat in which all end up in landfill (we were told not to put it in the plastic bin for recycling since it's dirty) - it just felt so wasteful :(

The spicy crunch congee is so flavorful! The whitefish sandwich was also really yummy. Which my friend had. The place is small but very "vibey." Super relaxing place to eat. The elderflower and ginger tea is super refreshing!

So glad we went out of our way to stop in for breakfast!  We shared the breakfast sandwich and congee. The spicy pork is amazing and the broccoli works really well! Both the bread and congee itself were fantastic too!

I'm officially obsessed with this place - best sandwich I have had in a long time (pork sando). Can't wait to go back to try the congee. Shop is small and cozy with lots of Asian pantry staples for sale. Get the matcha lemonade!

This is my favorite place in bed stuy. The owner and staff are incredibly personable, warm and kind. The prepared food is creative and delicious and the dry goods for sale on the shelves are affordable and also high quality. The sun streams in and there are plants everywhere and good music. It's perfect!
wonderful congee! try the ‘wake me up’ for brunch!  quick service, cozy atmosphere!
Tiny restaurant, but good coffee and delicious food, small menu. Wish they had bubble tea

Not your average breakfast sandwich, but SO, SO GOOD. I could talk about it for hours. Holy moley, I want another one like right now. Asian flavours, runny egg, perfect veg, amazing bread. Better than a BEC any day. Plus the tunes are pure decent

Tiny but super cute and friendly neighborhood cafe! Their “wake me up” congee with pork and broccoli is delicious and super filling. I had it in the height of the summer but I imagine it would be perfect winter comfort food as well.  I also loooove the selection of international flavors aside from their in-house menu — they sell East and South Asian brands of chili sauce, sesame oil, vinegar, wasabi powder and other sauces and condiments, plus a variety of local Brooklyn food/drink brands. They even have shrimp chips 😮

Charming trading post curated with local Brooklyn products and Asian goods, serving fresh roasted coffee, Thai iced coffee, matcha espresso and ice matcha lemonade with delicious breakfast and lunch sandwiches and their new Congee rice bowls. They've also got great vegetarian options and homemade baked goods.
Congee, SE Asian BK style. Also a shop with hard to find, authentic kitchen supplies.

A friend and I were looking for a unique place to get breakfast, and it was just that. I had a delicious egg sandwich, that had a kick. Provisions also sells  chopsticks, Asian spices, hot sauces and more that you can buy off the shelf.
Nice coffee shop.  I used to visit when it was on Lewis.  Great pastries, sandwiches and desserts.
Fast service, helpful employee, COMFORT food. I never had congee before. It's like a spicy warm hug.

Lived across the street for a short time. I don’t believe there is one tiny gem of REALLY AWESOME Asian flavor shop right next to me!! in the middle of Bedstuy. I’m Chinese and all the sauce/candies/snacks they have there are memory and some of them still my favorite.  The sandwich is awesome. the sauce and egg and pork belly is great, and the baguette(?) is crunchy and tasty.
Great service, really good food and really well made coffee/tea drinks.
Great neighborhood café
Love this place. Great congee + sandwiches. Can't go wrong. Fun atmosphere with big glasses windows/natural light. The sambal is absolutely amazing.

This spot is simply the bees knees! Delicious food (especially the congee), super welcoming space, lovely atmosphere & service. The owner is fantastic. There's no restroom available but everything else here is of such endearing quality that it doesn't even matter. I wish this little neighborhood place much success, it truly deserves it.
Quick service. Tasty egg with pork sandwhich on a nice roll.
The gentrified pork breakfast sandwich just changed my life. I'm still thinking about it.
Beautiful shop, delicious food!

I haven't been here but that looks like real italian bread seeded..I'm in California but was partially raised in Brooklyn..I miss that NY bread...I hate sour dough..when I visit Brooklyn to see family i will stop at Bed Stuy Provision.

The service was friendly and it was cool that they had some unique Korean and Japanese provisions, but the coffee is lackluster and the food way over priced for what you get. I got the breakfast sandwich and left still hungry.
I haven't physically visited yet, but I used to get their great breakfast sandwiches delivered when I was living in the area! I highly recommend. I need to make a point to get over there; good grub!

I really enjoyed their Vietnamese coffee, unique sandwiches and tasting Congee bowels. The owner who is there most of the time is extremely nice and her staff is on point when it comes to customer service. Which is very important to me. I always feel welcome when I come and by the taste of their food you can tell it's made with love.
Sooo DELICIOUS!!! I had the Biggie’s hoagie! Fire crackers in my mouth!!! The ladies are so sweet as well! Will definitely come back!
Super cozy space, great breakfast dishes/sandwiches and good service!
Great place, very limited menu and everything was amazing! Plus the roots Ska playlist by Matt in the kitchen was the perfect atmosphere. Thanks guys!
Pork belly sandwich to die for. Great atmosphere

Best spot in Bed Stuy for a delicious and affordable filling sandwich, get the pork belly and you will lose your mind! The owner is usually there and is very warm and welcoming, a lot of love and care has gone into this place!
They have really changed this area since I've used to be here years ago
the pork belly avocado is the best breakfast sandwich in Brooklyn. Unseats Bread & Spread. Good playlist too.
Food is worth the wait. Very well done and tasty!!
Expect slow service, but quality food especially for the neighborhood
Pork Underbelly Sandwiches are the rave.
The food is excellent and the staff is really nice. I only wished they were opened 7 days out of the week and closed little later than usual.

It is quaint and cozy. The atmosphere is friendly and laid back. The menu is simple, delicious, and organic. I live on the block and never tried it. Glad I made the stop this morning. Welcome to the neighborhood!!
Food and service were fantastic. Cozy little sandwich shop, unique atmosphere, food is fresh and made right where you can see it.
Its ok.
On the recommendation of our AirBnB host, we came for a sandwich - so so delicious! The PBLAT sandwich was outstanding. Local, excellent quality, everything fresh - thank you!
I saw a review somewhere that said they would walk up and down a hill twice if the breakfast sandwich was at the end and I have to agree (and I hate walking, and hills) truly delicious.
Good...
The wait staff is a little stiff and uncomfortable in their bodies
Small yet worth the wait. Well made food . Salad was so good.
Food quality
Delicious fresh food! The place is super cute although also super small.
The food was fresh and delicious. To top it off the owner was super sweet. Thank you for a great experience!
One of the best breakfast spots in Bed Stuy!!
All the sandwiches and salads I've tried are delicious!!
The breakfast sandwich with avocado is the best!!
Slamming sammies, great juices and damned good pretzels!!!
Small cafe with juices, soups, coffee, tea and hot and cold sandwiches
